Items which were left not done:

* A disc whose format was a hybrid of DOS physical layout and FileCore hard
disc layout can cause a 'Bad defect list' error when an attempt to format it
is made. This can be cured by only picking up and checking the defect list
in RetryDriveOp for Verify, ReadSecs, WriteSecs and Specify operations.
Other operations supplying a NIL defect list.
